HEADWORD: Phyton
<hw>Phy"ton</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Phytons</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>fyto`n</grk> plant.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of the parts
which by their repetition make up a flowering plant, each being a single
joint of a stem with its leaf or leaves; a phytomer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

